I"ù<p>Here in the DMV, Dempsey Hamilton owns and operates <a href="https://www.mobiusrecordshop.com/">Mobius Records</a> in Fairfax VA. Opening in 2014, Hamilton operated his store in a small building across from the stores current location. In 2016, he moved to a much larger space due to demand. Hamilton describes his record sales as Ã’sustainableÃ“ but noticed a significant increase in sales in the past few years.</p>

<p>Hamiltonâ€™s observations line up with <a href="https://www.riaa.com/reports/2021-mid-year-music-industry-revenue-report-riaa/">RIAA data</a>. Record sales jumped 216.6% between 2014 and 2020. In 2014, at the time of opening, vinyl sales were at 10.32 million. Last year, 22.36 million records were sold.</p>

