<p>According to RIAA data, the estimated value of vinyl in 2020 was around $12.2 billion. This is nearly double the value of records from the beginning of the decade to now. In addition, a 2018 poll of people 18-65 found that around 9% of people in the US listen to vinyl records. With COVID Lockdowns preventing people from visiting stores and streaming services dominating music consumption in the late 2010â€™s, how are vinyl records maintaining relevance?</p>

